<section class="section dark" id="entry"><p class="section-kicker">First 120 days</p><h2>Start with the system already in motion.</h2><p class="section-lede">Do not arrive with a generic maturity model. Read the portfolio, listen to operators and technical teams, then make one consequential workflow more legible before scaling the method.</p><div class="plan-strip"><article class="plan-phase"><span>Days 1-30</span><h3>Read the show</h3><p>Map strategy, architecture, portfolio, data and control boundaries, vendor dependencies, team capability and the current decision cadence. Listen at the frontline.</p></article><article class="plan-phase"><span>Days 31-60</span><h3>Name the contracts</h3><p>Establish portfolio intake, risk tiers, decision rights, technical standards, scorecard categories and the first AI Show Integrity Review.</p></article><article class="plan-phase"><span>Days 61-90</span><h3>Prove one run</h3><p>Select a bounded, measurable workflow. Baseline it, define human authority, test failure modes, instrument it and earn a production disposition.</p></article><article class="plan-phase"><span>Days 91-120</span><h3>Compound the learning</h3><p>Turn evidence into repeatable platform patterns, staffing priorities, vendor expectations, reusable controls and a transparent executive portfolio review.</p></article></div><div class="hero-actions"><a class="btn primary" href="120-day-plan.html">Open the detailed 120-day plan</a><a class="btn" href="show-integrity-review.html">Open the AI Show Integrity Review</a></div></section>
<section class="section gold"><div class="objection"><blockquote>“Where is the long résumé of production ML engineering leadership and the graduate AI degree?”</blockquote><div class="objection-answer"><p><strong>That is the right objection.</strong> My record does not support claiming a PhD, a career in model research, or years owning a named hyperscale MLOps platform. I would not blur that line.</p><p>My adjacent case is different: more than two decades leading engineering and high-consequence operations; current AI-first operating transformation; AI and automation workflow design since 2017; regulated autonomy and computer-vision concepts; 24/7 launch discipline; and a consistent ability to connect technical specialists, operators, governance actors and executives around mechanisms that hold under pressure.</p><p>The interview should test whether Universal needs only the deepest individual model builder - or a technical director who can recruit that depth, challenge it intelligently, create production discipline, and make AI valuable in the work.</p></div></div></section>
<section class="section white"><p class="section-kicker">Questions for executive discovery</p><h2>The answers determine the architecture.</h2><div class="questions"><div class="question"><p>Which guest or team-member moments have the clearest executive sponsorship for AI - and which are currently off limits?</p></div><div class="question"><p>Where does AI demand enter today, and who has authority to fund, stop or standardize it?</p></div><div class="question"><p>What separates an approved experiment from a production service at Universal Orlando?</p></div><div class="question"><p>Which dependencies create the greatest continuity risk: data, identity, vendors, APIs, cloud, devices or operating adoption?</p></div><div class="question"><p>How are human authority, override and escalation designed for guest-facing and operational decisions?</p></div><div class="question"><p>What evidence would make the first year unmistakably successful to D&amp;T, park operations and senior leadership?</p></div><div class="question"><p>Where is the current team strongest, and which technical or product capabilities must this director recruit or grow?</p></div><div class="question"><p>How do data science, platform engineering, product, cyber, privacy, legal and operations share production accountability?</p></div></div><p><a class="btn primary" style="margin-top:2rem" href="executive-questions.html">View the full executive question set</a></p></section>
<section class="section dark"><div class="artifact-cta"><div><p class="section-kicker">Application set</p><h2>One argument, different evidence surfaces.</h2><p class="section-lede">The resume, cover letter, interview brief, entry plan and review worksheet all reinforce the same proposition without duplicating the page.</p></div><div class="artifact-links"><a href="resume.html">Role-aligned resume</a><a href="cover-letter.html">Cover letter</a><a href="interview-brief.html">Interview thesis brief</a><a href="120-day-plan.html">120-day entry plan</a><a href="show-integrity-review.html">AI Show Integrity Review</a><a href="executive-questions.html">Executive questions</a></div></div></section>
